725083f-a.title: Queens: 19th Road - 78th Street
725083f-a.text:
19th Road, north side, at 78th Street, showing one of
the Rapelye houses, a colonial structure. The house stands
on what is the former Old Bowery Bay Road, a few yards inside
the limits of the old town of Long Island City, and dates back
prior to 1750. The old fawily burying-ground is directly be-
hind the house and can be seen on photographs bearing a 19th
Avenue location.
P. L. Sperr  June 3, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2,3
